In a different world, there is a different you.

&#x200B;

I know you are there, but not me.

&#x200B;

I would love to spend time with you, but I know you are there.

&#x200B;

I would love to talk about you, but I know you are there.

&#x200B;

I would love to read your eyes, but I know you are there.

&#x200B;

I would love to hear your voice, but I know you are there.

&#x200B;

I would love to look at your eyes, but I know you are there.

&#x200B;

I would love to see your smile, but I know you are there.

&#x200B;

I would love to hear your laugh, but I know you are there.

&#x200B;

I would love to be able to smile as you look at me, but I know you are there.

&#x200B;

